THE registration for the CEOs 2022 Luxury Retreat Golf tournament has officially started and the Minister for the Natural Resources and Tourism, Damas Ndumbaro is among them. Organised by Sea Cliff Resort and Spa Golf Club of Zanzibar, the annual event is scheduled to tee off on September 3rd this year at the 9-hole golf course located along the Indian Ocean sand beach. Sea Cliff Club manager Elias Soka told the ‘Sunday News’ from Zanzibar on Saturday that the registration of participants has officially started. Soka confirmed on Saturday that minister Ndumbaro is among those who have registered early for the event. “Registration is already open now and we only have 40 slots left. Online registration is available at  https://golfpad.events/event/3W9WC/registration. “So far we have 14 ladies from Eastern African countries who have confirmed to participate in this year's event, we may be having more ladies than gentlemen for the first time,” stressed Soka. Adding, said the registration is open through to August 31st, 2022. Soka commended CEOs tournament’s main sponsor Fumba Town Development for making it easy for them to start early preparations. He named others big sponsors as Exim Bank, Dodoma Wine, Castle lite, Com-Net, Rahisi solution Ltd, Fly Dubai and Sea Cliff Resort. “The door is still open for those wishing to join the sponsors’ list so as to make us organise a successful event, we welcome them all,” he noted. The day long 18-hole event will bring together CEOs, diplomats and other golfers from around the African continent and beyond. It will be played in stable ford format and is open for individual men and ladies with eligible handicap. Soka added that 50 US dollars is set as an entry fee for those wishing to take part in the event. The fee will include golf cart, half way lunch, gala dinner, practice access, soft drink and golf goodies bag. South African golfer Kyle Veitch is the defending champion.